## 7. Methodology

**Phase 1 (Year 1):** Formalize the Codec structure. Define N, E, λ, τ precisely. Prove basic properties: consistency, completeness relative to a chosen knowledge domain, and reconstructibility.

**Phase 2 (Year 2):** Implement SAOA. Build the orchestration architecture. Demonstrate construction of a bounded sub-graph (one civilization, one century) from heterogeneous source material.

**Phase 3 (Year 3):** Scale and validate. Extend to multiple civilizations. Test universality conditions. Characterize the meaning boundary formally.

**Phase 4 (Year 4):** Integrate with the Encyclopedia. Demonstrate the dual representation. Publish the full framework as an open, humanity-owned intellectual artifact.

